      <h2>Nature of Project</h2>
        <p class="lead" id='innerText'>
          This research project is conducted to investigate how
    people integrate information from various
    experiences (such as rewards received from multiple options) in
    decision making. In particular, this experiment examines how
    people's exploration and exploitation behaviour impact their performance. 
    In other words, do people start exploiting from one slot
    once they have experienced a large reward from it?
        </p>
        <p class="lead" id='innerText'>
          We are also interested in how the behavioural dynamics at a
    group-level are affected by the strategies and potential differences on the individual-level.
        </p>
